{
  "slug": "varroa-alcohol-wash-monitoring",
  "title": "Monitoring varroa with an alcohol wash",
  "subtitle": "Counting mites accurately to decide when to treat.",
  "excerpt": "A sticky board gives you a rough count of how many mites are dropping naturally. An alcohol wash gives you an actual mite load per 100 bees, the number that determines whether your colony needs treatment now or can wait. Here's how to do it.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
  "categorySlug": "animals-smallholding",
  "subCategorySlug": "bees",
  "difficulty": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "season": "SUMMER",
  "timeMinutes": 20,
  "sourceType": "SYNTHESISED",
  "sourceNotes": "NBU Beekeeper's Toolkit (2024), varroa-monitoring section. BBKA technical guidance on Varroa jacobsoni monitoring. Bee Craft column on mite-count methods.",
  "glossaryTerms": [],
