  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The alcohol wash gives a precise mite-to-bee ratio where a sticky board gives only a drop count that's impossible to standardise. A count of three or more mites per 100 bees in midsummer is the threshold at which most UK beekeeping guidance recommends treatment. Below that threshold, monitor monthly and treat in late summer once the supers are off regardless."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A jar or container with a fine-mesh lid (purpose-made varroa-wash jar or a mason jar with mesh screen replacing the disc)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Windscreen washer fluid or isopropyl alcohol, enough to cover the bee sample fully"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A white tray or white bowl to pour the wash into for counting"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A measuring spoon, roughly 100 bees is half a level 50 ml tablespoon by volume"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Taking the sample"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Find a frame of capped brood with nurse bees covering it. These are young bees with the highest mite loads."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shake or brush around 300 bees into the jar. Don't include the queen, if you can't be sure she's not on the frame, use a frame without her."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add enough alcohol to submerge the bees fully. Put the mesh lid on and shake vigorously for 30 seconds."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Counting the mites"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pour the alcohol wash through the mesh lid into the white tray. The mites wash through; the bees stay in the jar."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Count the mites in the tray. They're reddish-brown oval specks, clearly visible against white."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Estimate the number of bees used. Rinse and count the dead bees, or use the 300-bee volume as a divisor."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Calculate: (mite count ÷ bee count) × 100 = mites per 100 bees."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What the number means"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "NBU treatment thresholds"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The NBU recommends treating when the count reaches 3 or more mites per 100 bees during the active season (April to August). In late summer, once supers are off and brood is present, treat all colonies regardless of count. A zero count in midsummer is unusual, re-test on a different frame if you get an unexpectedly low result."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Recording the result"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Write the date and mite count in your apiary record alongside the colony ID. Monitoring every six weeks through summer gives you a trend line, a rising count is more informative than a single high reading."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
